71
00:07:56,612 --> 00:07:58,829
Okay?

72
00:07:59,003 --> 00:08:02,001
—Hey, Stringy!
—Yeah?

73
00:08:02,175 --> 00:08:04,478
Look how much I’ve got.

74
00:08:19,993 --> 00:08:24,731
<i>We came to the City of God
hoping to find paradise.</i>

75
00:08:24,904 --> 00:08:29,598
<i>Many families were homeless
due to flooding …</i>

76
00:08:29,728 --> 00:08:32,119
<i>and acts of arson
in the ghettos.</i>

77
00:08:32,379 --> 00:08:35,291
—A light post!
—We’ll have electricity!

78
00:08:35,508 --> 00:08:37,725
<i>The bigwigs in government
didn’t joke around.</i>

79
00:08:37,899 --> 00:08:40,811
<i>Homeless? Off to City of God!</i>

80
00:08:41,071 --> 00:08:45,070
<i>There was no electricity,
paved streets or transportation.</i>

81
00:08:45,330 --> 00:08:48,503
<i>But for the rich and powerful
our problems didn’t matter.</i>

82
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:51,675
<i>We were too far removed …</i>

83
00:08:51,893 --> 00:08:54,283
<i>from the picture postcard image
of Rio de Janeiro.</i>

84
00:09:11,058 --> 00:09:13,883
Do you think I can become
a lifeguard one day?

85
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,839
I don’t know.

86
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:18,924
Being a lifeguard is better
than a fishmonger.

87
00:09:19,098 --> 00:09:21,662
I don’t want to sell fish.
It stinks.

88
00:09:22,227 --> 00:09:24,531
—Are you insulting your father?
—No.

89
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:28,225
So what do you want to be?

90
00:09:28,703 --> 00:09:30,224
I don’t know.

91
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:34,048
—Not a hood or a policeman.
—Why not?

92
00:09:34,309 --> 00:09:36,482
I’m scared of getting shot.

93
00:09:40,915 --> 00:09:43,435
Put that thing away, kid.
Are you nuts?

94
00:09:43,566 --> 00:09:47,173
Pointing that gun at me?

95
00:09:47,347 --> 00:09:50,650
Take it easy with the kid, Goose.
Li’l Dice is with me.

96
00:09:50,780 --> 00:09:53,648
Right, I’m a gangster too.

97
00:09:53,866 --> 00:09:56,386
—That gas truck didn’t bring much.
—So what?

98
00:09:56,647 --> 00:10:00,298
—We rob gas trucks every day.
—One today, another tomorrow.

99
00:10:00,602 --> 00:10:02,775
No, we need to rob
some rich guy’s house.

100
00:10:02,992 --> 00:10:05,382
That’s the only
way to get outta here.

101
00:10:05,556 --> 00:10:08,903
Hell, no. What you need
is to follow my plan.

102
00:10:09,076 --> 00:10:10,554
That’s it.

103
00:10:10,771 --> 00:10:14,813
The little fart’s getting
too big for his britches!

104
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:24,157
He gets high and starts
talking bullshit.

105
00:10:24,331 --> 00:10:29,415
You two junkies aren’t worth
half as much as that kid.

106
00:10:31,241 --> 00:10:34,283
What you got in mind, Li’l Dice?

107
00:10:34,674 --> 00:10:39,237
<i>To be a real hood you need
more than just a gun. You need ideas.</i>

108
00:10:42,366 --> 00:10:44,496
<i>And Li’l Dice had them.</i>

109
00:10:45,669 --> 00:10:48,190
—Is that the motel?
—Yeah.

110
00:10:48,581 --> 00:10:53,275
We go in, grab the money and
get out. No killing, got that?

111
00:10:53,448 --> 00:10:56,882
—I need this.
—Don’t touch my gun, kid.

112
00:10:57,012 --> 00:10:58,229
Don’t ever do that again.

113
00:10:58,403 --> 00:11:00,098
—Don’t point at me.
—Fuck you.

114
00:11:00,228 --> 00:11:03,922
—Don’t point your finger at me!
—Stop acting like a baby!

115
00:11:04,661 --> 00:11:05,834
Here’s yours.

116
00:11:06,008 --> 00:11:08,485
—Awesome!
—Let’s go!

117
00:11:08,703 --> 00:11:11,223
—Not so fast!
—What?

118
00:11:11,441 --> 00:11:13,918
You stay here and keep watch.

119
00:11:14,135 --> 00:11:19,394
If the cops come, shoot that
window over there.

120
00:11:19,611 --> 00:11:22,610
—Why me? Let that dork do that.
—Look …

121
00:11:22,784 --> 00:11:27,955
I gave you this great plan, for free …
While that guy’s absolutely useless!

122
00:11:28,216 --> 00:11:29,911
—You just had the idea.
—Exactly!

123
00:11:30,085 --> 00:11:32,605
You’re just a kid, remember?

124
00:11:33,170 --> 00:11:35,952
You cover us, okay?

125
00:11:36,908 --> 00:11:41,775
You’ll get your turn, so cool it.
Stop trying to rush things.

126
00:11:41,993 --> 00:11:44,426
You stay there.

127
00:11:48,164 --> 00:11:51,336
This is a hold-up, bitch.

128
00:11:54,422 --> 00:12:01,115
You should be studying or working.
You don’t even look like hoodlums.

129
00:12:01,245 --> 00:12:05,243
Instead, you ought to be
working or studying, boy.

130
00:12:05,417 --> 00:12:08,416
Shut up!
What a pain in the arse!

131
00:12:09,285 --> 00:12:11,023
Okay, Clipper?

132
00:12:13,110 --> 00:12:14,544
Shall we go in?

133
00:12:20,020 --> 00:12:22,279
I didn’t order anything.

134
00:12:22,366 --> 00:12:26,538
It’s on the house, sir.
Hand over the money!

135
00:12:26,756 --> 00:12:29,016
Keep calm, all I want
is your cash.

136
00:12:29,146 --> 00:12:30,841
—Don’t point that …
—Your wallet …

137
00:12:43,314 --> 00:12:44,704
Hey, man …

138
00:12:44,922 --> 00:12:47,138
What kind of whorehouse is this?

139
00:12:50,267 --> 00:12:52,875
—You from the church?
—Yes, brother.

140
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:56,917
Give it to me!

141
00:12:59,090 --> 00:13:00,437
Slut!

142
00:13:00,654 --> 00:13:02,436
You’re old, fat and flabby!

143
00:13:03,349 --> 00:13:05,739
Wanna take her place?

144
00:13:10,172 --> 00:13:12,345
What’s going on?

145
00:13:13,475 --> 00:13:16,213
—The cops! Let’s beat it!
—Let’s go!

146
00:13:21,341 --> 00:13:24,817
Take that car.
I’ll go get Li’l Dice.

147
00:13:26,208 --> 00:13:28,729
Jesus, what a car!

148
00:13:34,596 --> 00:13:39,463
—Something fucked up. Li’l Dice’s gone.
—The cops are shooting, let’s go!

149
00:14:06,495 --> 00:14:08,885
Slow down! Hold on …

150
00:14:09,103 --> 00:14:11,840
—You said you knew how to drive.
—I do, so cool it!

151
00:14:12,101 --> 00:14:14,839
Turn! Watch out!

152
00:14:28,485 --> 00:14:30,267
You fucking arsehole!

153
00:14:31,180 --> 00:14:33,961
Hey, I didn’t do it on purpose.

154
00:14:34,135 --> 00:14:37,829
No one saw anything.
So keep your mouths shut, understand?

155
00:14:41,610 --> 00:14:44,609
Hold on, I twisted my ankle.

156
00:14:44,739 --> 00:14:46,999
Goose fucked up his ankle.

157
00:14:47,173 --> 00:14:48,173
It fucking hurts.

158
00:14:48,477 --> 00:14:52,345
Take him into the woods.
I’ll shoot to distract the cops.

159
00:14:52,562 --> 00:14:54,909
—In God we trust.
—In God we trust.

160
00:14:59,776 --> 00:15:02,080
Pass me the telephone, Penguin.

161
00:15:02,297 --> 00:15:06,165
<i>Shorty is another notorious guy
in the City of God.</i>

162
00:15:06,425 --> 00:15:08,381
<i>But it’s not yet time
to tell his story.</i>

163
00:15:10,293 --> 00:15:14,335
—It fucking hurts, Goose.
—Shut up.

164
00:15:15,030 --> 00:15:19,724
—Wait up …
—You sound like a damn sissy, man.

165
00:15:23,679 --> 00:15:26,938
<i>—Give me your hand! Climb up!
—No one saw anything?</i>

166
00:15:27,199 --> 00:15:32,023
How odd! A car crashes
into a bar and no one saw a thing.

167
00:15:32,240 --> 00:15:35,196
I suppose you didn’t see
anything either?

168
00:15:35,456 --> 00:15:39,237
As usual, no one saw,
no one knows.

169
00:15:39,933 --> 00:15:43,366
So what’s up, Shorty?

170
00:15:43,974 --> 00:15:46,843
They’re hiding in the woods.

171
00:15:47,842 --> 00:15:49,407
—Hello, Melon-head.
—How are you doing?

172
00:15:49,711 --> 00:15:53,101
I have this feeling that
they’re out in the woods.

173
00:15:53,362 --> 00:15:56,882
—The motherfuckers.
—They’re out in the woods.

174
00:15:57,708 --> 00:16:00,880
Felipe, lock up the car.
Rangel, come with me.

175
00:16:05,269 --> 00:16:08,616
I can’t see a thing.
How the hell can they see?

176
00:16:08,746 --> 00:16:11,223
Fucking jungle.

177
00:16:15,439 --> 00:16:19,568
—They stole a fortune at that motel.
—I know.

178
00:16:21,871 --> 00:16:24,565
What if we took the money?

179
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:29,216
Are you crazy?
I’m not getting mixed up in that.

180
00:16:29,346 --> 00:16:31,953
I want to exterminate these guys.

181
00:16:32,171 --> 00:16:36,430
What? Since when is stealing from
niggers and thieves a crime?

182
00:16:36,821 --> 00:16:43,427
It won’t be hard to nab them.
I have a stoolie in the City.

183
00:17:08,329 --> 00:17:15,022
—Did you hear those shots?
—If I catch one of them, I’ll kill him.

184
00:17:26,756 --> 00:17:28,320
Maracana!

185
00:17:28,668 --> 00:17:30,841
Open the door.

186
00:17:33,144 --> 00:17:36,795
—What’s the matter?
—The cops are after me.

187
00:17:45,226 --> 00:17:46,617
Shaggy!

188
00:17:47,877 --> 00:17:50,658
—Shaggy!
—The cops are on my arse!

189
00:17:50,832 --> 00:17:54,092
—Hide me!
—Quick, come in.

190
00:18:01,958 --> 00:18:06,260
Shit … I thought the cops
would be down there all night.

191
00:18:07,651 --> 00:18:10,519
I had a vision, Goose.

192
00:18:11,258 --> 00:18:14,083
You been smoking something?

193
00:18:14,431 --> 00:18:17,169
—You’ve had a job, right?
—Yeah.

194
00:18:17,386 --> 00:18:19,472
What’s it like?
What do people say?

195
00:18:19,733 --> 00:18:21,862
I worked with my father.

196
00:18:22,036 --> 00:18:25,600
And fathers talk a lot of shit.

197
00:18:26,817 --> 00:18:30,902
You know what, Goose?
I’m getting out, I don’t want to die.

198
00:18:31,032 --> 00:18:36,421
—This gangsters’ life isn’t for me.
—Wait! The cops are still down there.

199
00:18:36,595 --> 00:18:39,246
I don’t give a shit.

200
00:18:41,462 --> 00:18:44,113
I’m going back to the church.

201
00:18:44,765 --> 00:18:46,851
<i>He that dwells in the secret
place of the most High …</i>

202
00:18:47,069 --> 00:18:50,372
<i>shall abide under the shadow of
the Almighty. I will say of the Lord …</i>

203
00:18:50,589 --> 00:18:54,804
<i>He is my refuge and my fortress,
in Him will I trust.</i>

204
00:18:55,065 --> 00:18:58,325
<i>Fear not the terror by night,
nor the arrow that flies by day …</i>

205
00:18:58,498 --> 00:19:02,497
<i>nor the pestilence that walks
in darkness, nor the destruction …</i>

206
00:19:02,671 --> 00:19:06,582
—Stop, motherfucker!
—Don’t move!

207
00:19:06,886 --> 00:19:10,319
Stop, or I’ll shoot!

208
00:19:12,014 --> 00:19:17,012
<i>… shall abide under the shadow
of the Almighty.</i>

209
00:19:17,229 --> 00:19:21,967
<i>The hold-up at the motel went down
as the bloodiest in history.</i>

210
00:19:22,140 --> 00:19:25,052
<i>The destinies of the outlaws
then took different paths.</i>

211
00:19:25,269 --> 00:19:28,659
I don’t think this guy
was involved in the heist.

212
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:30,615
See here?

213
00:19:30,745 --> 00:19:36,221
—He’s a worker, not a hoodlum.
—I’ll make him one now.

214
00:19:39,481 --> 00:19:43,783
<i>Destiny put Clipper
back into the hands of God.</i>

215
00:19:45,261 --> 00:19:49,433
<i>Shaggy was in Bernice’s hands.</i>

216
00:19:51,128 --> 00:19:54,648
<i>And Goose was
in my father’s hands.</i>

217
00:19:54,822 --> 00:19:58,342
Why do you do these things?
You think I’m a fool?

218
00:19:58,559 --> 00:20:01,210
From now on,
you’ll work with me.

219
00:20:01,515 --> 00:20:05,643
Your younger brother
will keep an eye on you.

220
00:20:05,817 --> 00:20:07,816
You listen to me.

221
00:20:08,033 --> 00:20:12,379
If I catch you with money that
isn’t yours, I’ll kill you.

222
00:20:12,597 --> 00:20:18,464
That goes for you too. Get changed!
You start work immediately.

223
00:20:18,638 --> 00:20:24,374
<i>Having a hood as a brother sucks.
You always end up footing the bill.</i>

224
00:20:24,635 --> 00:20:28,894
Don’t worry.
Dad’s mad at me …

225
00:20:29,111 --> 00:20:33,414
but he’ll get over it.

226
00:20:36,673 --> 00:20:40,802
Give me that, Rocket. It’s not
for you. You have to study.

227
00:20:40,976 --> 00:20:44,279
—Getting shot doesn’t scare you?
—I’m a hood because I got no brain.

228
00:20:44,496 --> 00:20:48,320
But you’re smart.
You should study.

229
00:20:48,842 --> 00:20:52,188
I go to school because
I don’t like physical work.

230
00:20:52,710 --> 00:20:57,316
Promise me something …. That you’ll
never touch this gun. Promise?

231
00:20:57,968 --> 00:21:00,054
