They’re having fun,
and not me?

455
00:40:44,322 --> 00:40:46,538
I want to get out of here.

456
00:40:47,408 --> 00:40:51,536
What, kid? Your friend took
everything. What do you want?

457
00:40:57,664 --> 00:41:00,923
<i>That night, Li’l Dice
satisfied his thirst to kill …</i>

458
00:41:01,184 --> 00:41:03,748
<i>though he knew Shaggy would
never forgive him.</i>

459
00:41:11,093 --> 00:41:15,395
<i>To avoid being punished
he left the City of God.</i>

460
00:41:16,525 --> 00:41:19,220
<i>He had to work hard for peanuts.</i>

461
00:41:24,348 --> 00:41:27,477
<i>—Yeah, Benny!
—Li’l Dice and Benny managed well.</i>

462
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,389
<i>They had the gift of crime.</i>

463
00:41:31,606 --> 00:41:34,300
—You have more money than me.
—It was my idea.

464
00:41:34,474 --> 00:41:37,690
<i>The only problem was running into
an older hoodlum …</i>

465
00:41:37,864 --> 00:41:41,123
<i>… like my brother, Goose.
—Li’l Dice?</i>

466
00:41:41,297 --> 00:41:44,513
Shit, man. I thought
you were a goner at the motel.

467
00:41:44,817 --> 00:41:47,512
You’re fucking loaded!

468
00:41:47,686 --> 00:41:51,380
Don’t, Benny. That’s our money.

469
00:41:51,901 --> 00:41:56,291
Benny, tell your brother Shaggy …

470
00:41:56,551 --> 00:42:01,071
that Shorty is squealing.
I’m leaving the ghetto.

471
00:42:03,635 --> 00:42:05,113
Goose!

472
00:42:07,503 --> 00:42:10,893
From Shaggy. You’ll need it.

473
00:42:31,058 --> 00:42:33,622
<i>From one hit to the next,
Li’l Dice grew up.</i>

474
00:42:33,796 --> 00:42:38,142
<i>At 18, he was the most
respected hood in the City of God.</i>

475
00:42:38,403 --> 00:42:40,402
You’re of age now, watch out!

476
00:42:40,663 --> 00:42:44,009
<i>He was one of the most
wanted robbers in Rio.</i>

477
00:42:57,351 --> 00:42:58,916
Li’l Dice, how’s it going?

478
00:42:59,220 --> 00:43:02,740
Happy birthday.
I’m so glad you’ve turned 18 …

479
00:43:02,957 --> 00:43:06,217
—Get lost, Tuba!
—Excuse me, amigo …

480
00:43:06,869 --> 00:43:08,998
Give me a beer!

481
00:43:09,216 --> 00:43:12,692
Didn’t you see me, prick?

482
00:43:12,910 --> 00:43:14,778
—Sorry, man.
—Up yours!

483
00:43:15,039 --> 00:43:18,429
The next time,
I’ll waste you, arsehole!

484
00:43:19,820 --> 00:43:21,862
Fag!

485
00:43:22,166 --> 00:43:25,078
<i>Li’l Dice was ready for anything.</i>

486
00:43:25,339 --> 00:43:27,251
I wanna talk.

487
00:43:27,425 --> 00:43:30,424
<i>—And he was itching to start.
—Who are the fattest cats here?</i>

488
00:43:30,945 --> 00:43:35,074
—There are tons of them.
—Look at Jerry Adriani …

489
00:43:35,291 --> 00:43:39,376
gold chain, snazzy clothes.

490
00:43:39,594 --> 00:43:41,854
Look at Pereira
and the chick he’s with …

491
00:43:42,027 --> 00:43:45,982
—Bernice. She was my brother’s girl.
—Check out his car.

492
00:43:46,460 --> 00:43:50,545
Then there’s Blacky.
Covered in gold.

493
00:43:50,719 --> 00:43:53,414
Gold chain, gold watch …

494
00:43:53,718 --> 00:43:56,890
Look at Carrot, and his car.

495
00:43:57,151 --> 00:44:00,758
—They’re all dealers.
—They’re all fucking loaded.

496
00:44:00,976 --> 00:44:03,062
Hold-ups bring in chicken shit.

497
00:44:03,236 --> 00:44:06,017
—The big bucks are in drugs.
—I see.

498
00:44:06,278 --> 00:44:08,190
Especially in selling coke.

499
00:44:08,451 --> 00:44:10,667
—But you need money.
—Not really …

500
00:44:10,928 --> 00:44:14,578
We’ll kill these clowns
and take over their business.

501
00:44:14,752 --> 00:44:17,621
—When do we start?
—Now.

502
00:44:27,095 --> 00:44:31,006
Exu-the-Devil is the light
that shines forth.

503
00:44:31,310 --> 00:44:33,918
He brought you here.

504
00:44:34,135 --> 00:44:39,307
Why remain in the City of God
where God has forgotten you?

505
00:44:40,133 --> 00:44:44,522
I know what you want.
You want power.

506
00:44:44,826 --> 00:44:48,824
I have something which will
give it to you.

507
00:44:50,389 --> 00:44:54,909
To change your fate,
I give you my protector, boy.

508
00:44:55,169 --> 00:44:58,733
But you mustn’t fornicate
with the amulet …

509
00:44:58,994 --> 00:45:01,297
otherwise …

510
00:45:02,340 --> 00:45:04,861
you’ll die.

511
00:45:05,295 --> 00:45:07,773
The boy is no longer called
Li’l Dice …

512
00:45:07,903 --> 00:45:09,946
but Li’l Zé.

513
00:45:10,163 --> 00:45:13,727
Li’l Zé will grow up.

514
00:45:14,031 --> 00:45:17,768
You stick with me,
I’ll stick with you.

515
00:45:29,111 --> 00:45:32,458
<i>Li’l Dice became Li’l Zé
and he began to kill.</i>

516
00:45:33,544 --> 00:45:40,324
<i>He started one morning,
taking over Jerry Adriani’s racket.</i>

517
00:45:41,497 --> 00:45:45,887
<i>By that night, almost all
of the rackets in the ghetto were his.</i>

518
00:45:46,060 --> 00:45:49,537
<i>The only business he didn’t
touch was Carrot’s …</i>

519
00:45:49,711 --> 00:45:53,666
<i>since he was a friend of Benny’s.
All that was left was the apartment …</i>

520
00:45:53,840 --> 00:45:54,970
<i>But that would be easy.</i>

521
00:45:59,750 --> 00:46:02,792
Who is it?

522
00:46:09,572 --> 00:46:11,397
—Hey, Blacky.
—Fuck, Li’l Dice.

523
00:46:11,658 --> 00:46:17,742
—You show up like this at my place?
—Who said it was your place?

524
00:46:17,916 --> 00:46:19,524
—Something wrong, Li’l Dice?
—Li’l Dice, my arse.

525
00:46:19,785 --> 00:46:23,218
—My name is Li’l Zé now.
—His name’s Li’l Zé, see?

526
00:46:23,392 --> 00:46:26,521
—You’re a goner, bastard.
—Don’t kill him. He understands.

527
00:46:26,695 --> 00:46:28,911
Right, Blacky?

528
00:46:29,129 --> 00:46:33,605
It’s all yours, I don’t want anything.
I don’t want no trouble, okay?

529
00:46:33,735 --> 00:46:36,995
<i>I should have taken this chance
to avenge my brother’s death.</i>

530
00:46:38,820 --> 00:46:43,427
You’ll live, but you’ll
work for us. Understand?

531
00:46:43,601 --> 00:46:45,687
<i>That’s easy to say …</i>

532
00:46:47,164 --> 00:46:50,380
—Where are you going?
—He’s clean, Li’l Zé.

533
00:46:50,858 --> 00:46:52,292
What’s your name, kid?

534
00:46:52,510 --> 00:46:56,291
—Rocket.
—He’s Goose’s brother.

535
00:46:56,508 --> 00:46:59,116
—Goose?
—The late Goose.

536
00:47:00,332 --> 00:47:02,549
Quick, kid. Run along.

537
00:47:02,897 --> 00:47:07,329
Tell everyone that this business
now belongs to Li’l Zé.

538
00:47:07,503 --> 00:47:11,415
And that we’ll be selling coke.
Got that?

539
00:47:11,762 --> 00:47:13,457
Cocaine.

540
00:47:16,543 --> 00:47:19,411
—Where’s the turf?
—Over there, on the left.

541
00:47:19,672 --> 00:47:22,627
<i>Selling drugs is like any
other business.</i>

542
00:47:23,018 --> 00:47:24,930
<i>The supplier
delivers the merchandise …</i>

543
00:47:25,148 --> 00:47:27,842
<i>which is then
packaged on the premises.</i>

544
00:47:28,190 --> 00:47:31,927
<i>It’s done in an assembly line.</i>

545
00:47:32,101 --> 00:47:34,187
<i>Boring as hell …</i>

546
00:47:34,709 --> 00:47:38,664
<i>Pot is wrapped up in “lids”.</i>

547
00:47:38,968 --> 00:47:41,662
<i>Cocaine is put into packets …</i>

548
00:47:42,314 --> 00:47:46,573
<i>and then into bundles
of 10 or 100.</i>

549
00:47:47,095 --> 00:47:49,833
<i>You can even make a career
in dealing drugs.</i>

550
00:47:50,006 --> 00:47:53,874
<i>The kids start out
as delivery boys.</i>

551
00:47:54,135 --> 00:47:58,177
<i>They’re paid to run errands
and take messages.</i>

552
00:47:59,046 --> 00:48:02,045
<i>Then they become lookouts.
If the police arrive …</i>

553
00:48:02,175 --> 00:48:05,043
<i>the kites disappear
and everyone scrams.</i>

554
00:48:06,217 --> 00:48:09,867
<i>Later, you become a dealer
or a “vapour”.</i>

555
00:48:10,085 --> 00:48:13,127
<i>When the heat’s on, the
“vapour” quickly evaporates.</i>

556
00:48:13,431 --> 00:48:17,429
<i>Moving up the ladder
you have the “soldier”.</i>

557
00:48:17,777 --> 00:48:21,341
<i>And if the guy is good at maths,
he can become a manager …</i>

558
00:48:21,558 --> 00:48:25,078
<i>the boss’ right-hand man.</i>

559
00:48:26,425 --> 00:48:30,337
<i>The police receive their cut
and don’t make trouble.</i>

560
00:48:32,597 --> 00:48:35,248
<i>Since Li’l Zé killed off
all of his enemies …</i>

561
00:48:35,378 --> 00:48:40,332
<i>there were no shoot-outs in the
City of God. You could drive there …</i>

562
00:48:40,680 --> 00:48:44,244
<i>The playboys felt safe
buying their drugs there.</i>

563
00:48:45,721 --> 00:48:50,328
<i>The City teemed with addicts
and Li’l Zé grew rich.</i>

564
00:48:51,241 --> 00:48:53,588
—Is it okay?
—It’s a deal.

565
00:48:57,238 --> 00:49:01,323
—I can’t decide which to wear.
—This one’s cool.

566
00:49:02,192 --> 00:49:06,408
<i>If dealing were legal, Li’l Zé
would have been man of the year.</i>

567
00:49:09,841 --> 00:49:12,797
<i>But things were risky for me.
I was afraid of him.</i>

568
00:49:13,014 --> 00:49:17,186
<i>—And he was everywhere.
—What a drag this guy is.</i>

569
00:49:17,403 --> 00:49:22,488
<i>Whenever I wanted to smoke a joint
I had to go see Carrot.</i>

570
00:49:27,138 --> 00:49:30,050
Half a lid. Thanks.

571
00:49:31,180 --> 00:49:35,309
<i>But it was worth it.
I only smoked with Angélica.</i>

572
00:49:37,047 --> 00:49:39,872
<i>She and Thiago had split up,
so I made my move.</i>

573
00:49:40,089 --> 00:49:45,869
<i>—I was about to win her over …
—These pictures are really great.</i>

574
00:49:46,086 --> 00:49:49,650
—You think so?
—I look good here.

575
00:49:49,824 --> 00:49:52,605
—You look beautiful everywhere.
—I’m serious.

576
00:49:52,866 --> 00:49:53,866
Me too.

577
00:49:56,691 --> 00:50:01,949
<i>A setting sun,
a deserted beach … a long kiss …</i>

578
00:50:02,123 --> 00:50:05,165
<i>I was sure this was it …</i>

579
00:50:05,730 --> 00:50:08,033
<i>But the Runts arrived.</i>

580
00:50:08,685 --> 00:50:11,988
Can I have a toke?

581
00:50:17,594 --> 00:50:18,811
Here.

582
00:50:19,029 --> 00:50:23,244
I’m going. See you later.

583
00:50:24,939 --> 00:50:28,329
Hold on, Angélica.

584
00:50:28,503 --> 00:50:31,067
—Your joint, man.
—Keep it.

585
00:50:31,241 --> 00:50:33,588
What a cool guy.

586
00:50:36,456 --> 00:50:40,976
<i>That was my first run
in with the Runts.</i>

587
00:50:46,799 --> 00:50:49,841
—Steak and fries, Benny.
—Great! Here …

588
00:50:53,362 --> 00:50:59,272
—A tip for you.
—Really? Thanks.

589
00:50:59,533 --> 00:51:01,793
—Wanna eat something?
—No.

590
00:51:05,052 --> 00:51:09,181
<i>—Wanna trade this watch?
—After Angélica left him …</i>

591
00:51:09,398 --> 00:51:11,310
<i>Thiago began snorting
more and more.</i>

592
00:51:11,571 --> 00:51:14,657
—Is it your grandfather’s?
—No, my dad’s.

593
00:51:14,917 --> 00:51:19,133
<i>When a guy is really hooked
he ends up in the hands of the dealer.</i>

594
00:51:19,350 --> 00:51:21,436
—Two bags of ten.
—One of ten.

595
00:51:21,610 --> 00:51:25,739
<i>—Okay, one bag.
—For Thiago, it was different.</i>

596
00:51:25,956 --> 00:51:29,520
—Watch out!
—Sorry, godfather.

597
00:51:29,867 --> 00:51:32,605
Godfather, my arse.
Did I baptise your kids?

598
00:51:32,866 --> 00:51:35,821
—I’m sorry.
—Now beat it.

599
00:51:38,516 --> 00:51:42,427
Blacky, lend me your bike.

600
00:52:05,982 --> 00:52:08,242
Hey, wanna race?

601
00:52:08,416 --> 00:52:11,893
—Where to?
—Up to the highway.

602
00:52:12,458 --> 00:52:15,456
—Okay.
—Ready? Go!

603
00:52:37,838 --> 00:52:41,662
—Pretty tough, wasn’t it?
—Yeah, you’re good.

604
00:52:41,923 --> 00:52:44,226
Where’d you buy those sneakers?

605
00:52:44,400 --> 00:52:47,008
—Not far from here.
—The shirt, as well?

606
00:52:47,182 --> 00:52:49,572
—No, uptown.
—Cool.

607
00:52:49,746 --> 00:52:52,006
It’s a designer shirt.

608
00:52:52,266 --> 00:52:54,483
If I give you money
can you buy me one?

609
00:52:54,787 --> 00:52:57,395
Shorts and a shirt?

610
00:52:59,654 --> 00:53:01,914
Buy whatever you can.

611
00:53:04,565 --> 00:53:06,738
—What size are you?
—Measure me.

612
00:53:06,869 --> 00:53:09,824
—With what, man?
—Shit, with your hand.

613
00:53:11,258 --> 00:53:13,996
Shoe size? Turn around.

614
00:53:22,818 --> 00:53:27,729
—Hey, Benny!
—You got the digs?

615
00:53:30,771 --> 00:53:34,118
—Just one pair of pants?
—No, there’s more.

616
00:53:39,159 --> 00:53:40,376
—You like it?
—Yeah.

617
00:53:41,636 --> 00:53:43,983
There’s some change.

618
00:53:44,505 --> 00:53:47,547
—Keep it.
—Cool.

619
00:53:56,021 --> 00:53:58,716
This is Benny.

620
00:53:59,759 --> 00:54:03,322
—This is Rocket.
—Hi. I know him.

621
00:54:27,834 --> 00:54:30,441
I’ve become a playboy.

622
00:54:32,440 --> 00:54:36,569
Hey, gangsters, listen to this …

623
00:54:36,743 --> 00:54:38,611
Watch out …

624
00:54:38,785 --> 00:54:42,392
Groovies shake their arses
before laying a big one.

625
00:54:45,869 --> 00:54:47,694
Oh, yeah?

626
00:54:48,520 --> 00:54:51,171
Fuck off, you bastards!

627
00:54:53,518 --> 00:54:57,473
Making fun of me?

628
00:54:58,777 --> 00:55:00,819
Arsehole!

629
00:55:15,682 --> 00:55:19,898
Benny, didn’t I tell you to shoot Carrot?
He’s endangering the ghetto.

630
00:55:20,159 --> 00:55:23,679
—Cool it. Go talk to him.
—I’m gonna kill that fucker.

631
00:55:23,853 --> 00:55:26,764
—Stop trying to wipe out everyone.
—I’m gonna kill him.

632
00:55:29,068 --> 00:55:32,023
Don’t worry, Angélica.
The guys in here are cool.

633
00:55:32,284 --> 00:55:34,978
Sure, I’m not worried.

634
00:55:35,369 --> 00:55:39,237
You gonna dance, Benny?
What about Carrot?

635
00:55:39,411 --> 00:55:43,496
Go on, buddy. Go talk to the guy.

636
00:55:43,714 --> 00:55:47,277
<i>Benny was the coolest hood
in the City of God.</i>

637
00:55:47,495 --> 00:55:50,667
<i>He gave away pot,
paid for drinks.</i>

638
00:55:51,145 --> 00:55:54,231
<i>Li’l Zé was the opposite.
He had one obsession:</i>

639
00:55:54,405 --> 00:55:56,404
<i>To be the boss of the ghetto.</i>

640
00:55:56,621 --> 00:55:59,880
<i>He wanted an excuse to take over
Carrot’s racket.</i>

641
00:56:00,011 --> 00:56:01,749
—Hey, Carrot.
—What’s up?

642
00:56:01,923 --> 00:56:06,182
You shouldn’t let the Runts
do hold-ups in the ghetto.

643
00:56:06,790 --> 00:56:09,615
You look after your section,
I’ll look after mine.

644
00:56:09,789 --> 00:56:13,614
Got that? I’m gonna get a drink.

645
00:56:21,523 --> 00:56:26,478
—Hey, Rocket! How’s it going?
—Great.

646
00:56:26,651 --> 00:56:29,694
—Hey, Benny!
—How’s it going?

647
00:56:30,389 --> 00:56:33,388
—Hey, Thiago. How are you?
—Good.

648
00:56:34,387 --> 00:56:35,952
—May I?
—Sure …

649
00:56:36,169 --> 00:56:38,429
Wanna dance?

650
00:56:41,949 --> 00:56:45,426
—Is it okay at your place?
—No problem.

651
00:56:45,643 --> 00:56:49,294
My parents are out.
You’ll be all alone with her.

652
00:56:49,555 --> 00:56:53,900
—You can lose your virginity tonight.
—Not so loud, man!

653
00:56:54,074 --> 00:56:55,769
Everyone will hear.

654
00:56:57,116 --> 00:56:59,376
—You’re beautiful.
—Thank you.

655
00:56:59,637 --> 00:57:04,113
—Shit!
—Nothing’s happening.

656
00:57:11,284 --> 00:57:15,674
Look, man, I know the Runts
are associated with you.

657
00:57:15,847 --> 00:57:19,498
Think I’m a sucker, you little brat?
You want to take my racket?

658
00:57:19,715 --> 00:57:23,887
I want to talk to you
because you’re fucking useless.

659
00:57:24,105 --> 00:57:25,104
Get your hand away!

660
00:57:25,322 --> 00:57:28,320
The Runts are screwing up
our security, man.

661
00:57:28,538 --> 00:57:29,885
Give the baby his bottle.

662
00:57:30,015 --> 00:57:32,492
Carrot, just ask the kids
to cool it, okay?

663
00:57:32,666 --> 00:57:36,099
Carrot’s useless. He lets the Runts
do hold-ups in his section.

664
00:57:36,273 --> 00:57:39,272
The police come around and
that’s bad for business.

665
00:57:39,533 --> 00:57:43,140
I’ll do it only because
I like you.

666
00:57:43,444 --> 00:57:45,139
But you need to change
that baby’s diapers.

667
00:57:45,269 --> 00:57:49,137
I’ll show you who’s the baby …

668
00:57:49,311 --> 00:57:54,830
Tell the kids that in my ghetto
no one robs or rapes!

669
00:57:55,004 --> 00:57:56,525
No wonder you’re “Little” Zé!

670
00:57:59,654 --> 00:58:04,739
<i>The Runts were kids who didn’t
respect the laws of the ghetto.</i>

671
00:58:04,870 --> 00:58:08,259
<i>They would mug residents,
hold-up bakeries …</i>

672
00:58:08,433 --> 00:58:10,650
<i>especially in Carrot’s section.</i>

673
00:58:13,648 --> 00:58:17,256
What are you doing?

674
00:58:18,950 --> 00:58:23,514
<i>—You rob me all the time!
—But they didn’t know …</i>

675
00:58:23,644 --> 00:58:26,034
<i>that the City had a boss now.</i>

676
00:58:27,860 --> 00:58:29,902
<i>Thank You for Choosing Us</i>

677
